text: Theophano () may refer to: *Theophano of Athens, consort of Staurakios (reigned 811) *Theophano Martinakia, first consort of Leo VI the Wise (reigned 886 - 912) *Theophano (born Anastaso), consort of Romanos II (reigned 959 - 963) and Nikephoros II (reigned 963 - 969) *Theophanu, consort of Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor (reigned 967 - 983) *Theophanu, Abbess of Essen from 1039â€“1058, granddaughter of Empress Theophanu and Otto II
title: Theophano
